- "gathered a crowd of more than five critics" refers to movies that have more than 5 ratings;
- "sparkle with the highest average ratings" refers to the highest average ratings calculated from the ratings;
- "top three" refers to the three highest-ranked movies based on their average ratings.

- "Prolific" refers to a director who has directed more than 2 movies;
- "Highly-rated films" refers to movies with a rating above the average rating of all movies;
- "Early 2000s" refers to the period between the years 2000 and 2010.

- 'Free' users are those with a 'free' subscription type;
- 'Highly rated' refers to movies with an aggregate rating greater than 80;
- 'Top 5' is determined by ranking movies based on their average rating and number of recommendations.

- "highly-rated cinematic gems" refers to movies with an average rating greater than 4.5;
- "premium subscribers" refers to users with a 'premium' subscription type;
- "shining like stars in the night sky" is a metaphor for being highly recommended and well-received.

- 'Highly rated' implies a high average rating;
- 'Majority of ratings above 4' means more than 50% of the ratings are greater than 4;
- 'Western' is a genre of movies.

- 'Interactions' refer to actions like liking, saving, or sharing a movie;
- 'Watch history' includes the dates and durations users spent watching movies;
- 'User ratings' are the numerical values given by users to rate movies.

- "top 3 jewels" refers to the top 3 movies with the highest average ratings in each genre;
- "shining the brightest" refers to having the highest average ratings;
- "each genre's crown" refers to the genre classification of the movies.
